      "message": "I mean, when name\u003d\u003dGL_EXTENSIONS, in the situation when (1) len(before)\u003d\u003d0 (2) glProtocolStr.size()\u003e0, this function ends up telling the guest that len\u003dglProtocolStr.size(). But the snprintf would eventually write glProtocolStr.size()+1 bytes into the buffer (+1 is the string ending byte). Does it make sense?",
